{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04820/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04820"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:48:20"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["dirty single"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman smiles at another woman seated across from her."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04820/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04820","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04820/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04820"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04820/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04820/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04820/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04820/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04820/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04820/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04820/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04820/canvas/1/3794c235-5a1d-4214-bc93-1cd5b250abf7","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T19:18:07.704Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The beginning of this scene opens with a shot-reverse shot between Cyril and Alma. The audience is not aware that Reynolds is present in the room until the shot opens up later, breaking the suture of the women’s relationship.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04820/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:37.229966777683785,36.81150516871192,346.3626292466764,295.78332717872973"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04820/canvas/1/150d9023-2e24-438b-9f51-2158f3f21594","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T19:18:54.288Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW133378539 BCX0\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-03942.html\"><u>Once again</u></a>, the striking light on the left side of Cyril’s face divides her visage in half. Here, however, the dynamic has shifted. Rather than positioning Reynolds as the source of dominating illumination, there is opacity in the shared moment between Cyril and Alma that excludes him. It is the shadow that enables a reorientation of the relationship between these women. Alma has now asserted a position of importance within the triangular dynamic of the House of Woodcock, allowing her to exist alongside Cyril outside of her relationship to Reynolds.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04820/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:509.2134416669008,148.41831831494542,425.5654542097489,809.0611152141802"}}}]}]}]}